Can you look at someone's damage histogram or average damage per hit and tell me exactly how much mitigation AC they had <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> without</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> knowing exactly how mitigation AC functions? Since testing how much benefit you get from each point of mitigation AC is the whole purpose of the tests, it is pointless not to isolate it from other variables. <br>
<br>
Trying to evaluate mitigation AC tests without knowing how much mitigation AC the subject had is a very poor way to come up with data. That's like trying to find out how many miles per gallon your car gets without an accurate odometer or any other way to measure distance travelled. Have fun guessing. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
