<br>
Check out some old MUD/MUSH code Smush, it'll give you an idea how things could have been set up.  Bottom line is whatever they did will be EXTREMELY efficient- definitely no floating point calculations, probably overlays and bitshifts or other fast and dirty algorithms.  Rounding won't be smooth, and variables should change in discrete increments, not linearly (stair steps, bit sized or bigger, not a straight line).  <br>
<br>
Because of the way the RNG works (using a time-varying seed, at least partially tick based apparently), and the probability that a random number generated has some finite &quot;lifetime&quot; and might be reused in several calculations, figuring out the ORDER in which checks are made during combat could also yield... interesting results.<br>
<br>
For the amount of combat that goes on, there's no other way (I know of anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) to implement it w/o requiring WAY more cpu than is realistic.<br>
<br>
RdT.<br>
p.s. personal opinion is that AC mitigation is *effectively* capped by expansion, while avoidance is capped by skill, level delta (also expansion dependent<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and stat (agi).  Perfectly consistent with what has been tested/reported... but makes you wonder what will happen with AC in PooPoo.  Don't delete that high AC gear just yet imho... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/19/02 10:27:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: softcap</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Golems in ST.. I have 1428 ac with raid buffs get hit for max of 316. Other tank has 1258 ac max hit of 316. These are non defensive hits. Now the SKs in the raid report max hits of 285.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
